news.title: Saint-Gobain aims for double-digit operating margin in 2024
news.para: In a call with journalists, Bazin added that there is a "structural unmet need for housing" in Western Europe, North America and Asia, which could reverse the new-construction division's downward curb.

news.title: Spain's Inmobiliaria Colonial reports net loss of $1.10 billion in 2023
news.para: Real estate companies such as Colonial and its peer Merlin Properties earn profit on the rental of their assets and have to include in their results the impact of an updated valuation of their properties conducted every six months.

news.title: Ireland: Glenveagh Properties & Cairn Homes eye big growth in state-partnered projects
news.para: Despite recovering to a 15-year high of almost 33,000 units last year, new housing supply in Ireland has for a decade failed to keep up with demand. Analysts say closer to 50,000 homes are needed a year as the economy and population grows strongly.

news.title: New home prices in China rise by 0.14% in February 2024: Survey
news.para: The average new home price across 100 cities rose 0.14%, compared with an on-month gain of 0.15% in January, showed data from real estate researcher China Index Academy.

news.title: Evos Alchemy: Elevating luxury living in Odisha by  Evos Buildcon Pvt Ltd
news.para: Developed by Evos Buildcon Pvt Ltd, this visionary project promises residents a lifestyle of gold-class living, reshaping the future of real estate in Odisha and beyond.

news.title: Deutsche Bank to file liquidation suit against China's Shimao Group: Sources
news.para: Shanghai-based Shimao is among the many Chinese developers that have defaulted on offshore bonds, after it missed the interest and principal payment for a $1 billion offshore bond in July, 2022.

news.title: China Evergrande chairman's second seized Hong Kong mansion put up for sale
news.para: Evergrande, the world's most indebted property developer which defaulted its offshore debt in late 2021, was liquidated by a Hong Kong court in January.

news.title: China sets deadline for cities to set up financing coordination mechanism for property projects
news.para: Financial institutions need to prevent loans from being misappropriated and safeguard the safety of credit funds, the Chinese housing ministry's newspaper China Real Estate Business reported, citing a meeting held on Thursday.

news.title: Trinity Infratech partners with Seetu Kohli to bring one-of-a-kind residences furnished with Versace homes to Gurgaon
news.para: Seetu Kohli, a prominent name in India's design fraternity, brings her impeccable taste and vision to this project, ensuring that every aspect of the residence exudes elegance and luxury.

news.title: Maharashtra government plans transit-oriented development near metro, monorail stations
news.para: The state government plans to increase footfalls in Metro and monorail by introducing a new regulation for transit-oriented development (TOD) zones.

news.title: Mumbai police arrests SVK project LLP directors for defrauding flat buyers
news.para: Manoj Champaklal Shah, 72, and Suresh Shroff, 65, directors of SVK project LLP, were arrested by the Economic Offences Wing's Unit 2 for defrauding 10 flat buyers of Rs 11.50 crores in a redevelopment project in Vile Parle.

news.title: Rajasthan HC provides relief to plot owner after Jaipur Development Authority fails to provide promised facilities
news.para: The "impugned order dated 19.01.2024 passed by learned single judge deserves to be and is accordingly, quashed and set aside" on the ground of lack of jurisdiction, it said.

news.title: About 29 applications received at Kanpur development body's mutation camp
news.para: ​​​Maximum 10 applicants were of zone-1, 4, 5, seven applicants of zone-2 ,3 and 4, two applicants were from the World Bank and one from the rental property department.

news.title: New software to tackle delay, loss of property tax revenue in Pune
news.para: The move will help the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) bring properties under the property tax ambit immediately after the grant of an occupancy certificate (OC) or get registered.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body plans GIS-based survey to track taxes
news.para: As part of this project, the civic body will use latest high-resolution satellite data and drones to capture boundaries of each plot and building.

news.title: Special drive in Telangana from March 1-9 to clear 2.4 lakh Dharani applications
news.para: Principal secretary (revenue) Navin Mittal, who is also chief commissioner of land administration, asked the collectors to constitute 2-3 teams in every tahsildar office limits to scrutinise, undertake field inspections and prepare reports.

news.title: No action against owner of illegal building, Gurugram civic body engineers to face action
news.para: MCG is planning to seek action against one junior and two assistant engineers under Rule 7 (major penalty) of the Haryana Civil Services (Punishment and Appeal) Rules, 2016, for failing to take action against the property owner.

news.title: About 100% hike in collectorate guideline rates proposed in five locations near Bhopal metro
news.para: According to assessment, expected completion of Bhopal metro is in 2026. It includes two lines, one under-construction Karond to AIIMS Bhopal. Another is Bhadbhada to Ratnagiri.

news.title: Gujarat assembly passes amendment bill on transfer fees collected by housing societies
news.para: ​​​​​Through an amendment, the BJP government inserted a new section in the Gujarat Co-operative Societies Act, 1961, which says "a co-operative housing society or a cooperative housing service society shall not collect transfer fee more than the transfer fee as may be prescribed".

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to carry out 'voluntary' Aadhaar seeding of property records
news.para: The Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) is expecting a total receipts of Rs 12,371.63 crore comprising its opening balance of Rs 8,294.04 crore and central and state grants of Rs 4,077.59 crore.
